embeddings.text: Silver Valley: An immersive system merging in-game & after-game experiences with real stories from elderly interviews, fostering intergenerational connections.
Kleshas: Kleshas is a generative art project which aims to visualize and simulate negative emotions derived from Buddhist concepts in a virtual ecological environment.

Excavating Eternal Beings - A Past Life Regression: Audiovisual installation telling the story of my future incarnation on a past life regression, discovering the patterns throughout 9 lifetimes and continuing her life journey with a change.
Daydreams of Simulacra (Hallucinated Voicemail): Interactive sculpture reflecting on humanity in the age of artificial intelligence and machine learning simulation.

Don’t Look At Me When I’m Coding: As a programmer, the artist perceives coding as a delightful craft. This installation seeks to discuss the place and emotions of individuals in their work, regardless of the nature of the job or the era.

Body Domain: "Body Domain" is a multimedia installation that examines the juxtaposition of aging body and dancer movement, curating a space for movement and offering the artist's interpretation of the effects of aging.
Before the Sun Rises: Re-growing a dying land with kindred spirits of the forest.
Nesting: The Non-Human Technology of Bird Nests: Learning from the non-human technologies, extraordinary craft, and ritual behaviors involved in birds’ practice of building nests and creating homes.
I Made A Miro Board: A digital readymade artwork; create a safe yet brave place to trigger discussions and debates.

Sleepy Paradise: A digital application that generates audio-visual experiences for the elderly to use for personal practices, aiming to help them sleep better, feel more relaxed and positive via nature therapy and music therapy.
Ecstasy and Dissolution: I’ve created a soundscape protocol and series of soundbaths that guide audience members into elusive states of consciousness with my real-time heart and brainwave activity.
Delete Me: "Delete Me” is an exploration in data collection, digital rights, and the catharsis of participatory destruction

Classifier: An interactive installation aims to challenge and provoke critical reflection on facial emotion recognition systems, highlighting the complex nature of emotions and the potential risks associated with such technology.

FutureCraft: A Collaborative World Building System: FutureCraft is a collaborative card game that uses AR to help players explore the potential consequences of their decisions and build a better future together.

The Wheel of Anxiety: How to deal with the pervasive and unavoidable anxiety in my life?
“When you gaze into the abyss, the abyss also gazes at you." So it is with Anxiety.
Interactive Theatre in the Digital Age: Extending the impact and reach of live theatre and performance beyond the limitations of a physical stage.

Merging Worlds: bridging analog and digital photography: Inspired by my personal experiences as a software engineer and analog photographer, this project is a personally crafted camera that blends the tactile charm of analog photography with discreet incorporation of digital features.

Beyond The Spectrum: Beyond The Spectrum is an immersive, illustrative exhibition that uses illustrations, audio, and chalk footsteps as a way to pay homage to the significant African Americans and their contributions throughout history.

Self Talk to Self Confidence: Inspiring Women through Positive Affirmations: Spread-positivity.com is a website that connects women and gives them access to community-generated positive affirmations to help build confidence, improve self-esteem, and build a support network. The site synthesizes current affirmation-building best practices and equips women with tools to craft more impactful and effective positive affirmations for use in their daily lives.
lush foliage and flourishing branches: The continuation of life and memories
Reduce Your Time Waste: An app that helps reduce doom scrolling using goal setting and positive reinforcement to refocus wasted online time into offline fun.

Perceptible Radio Waves: Perceptible Radio Waves is an exploration into a ubiquitous, yet normally imperceptible phenomena that drives modern telecommunication. This is a device that guides an audience through contemplation of what radio waves are, how they have become nearly inescapable in our modern society, and allows space to reflect how this could be effecting our lives.

Seatizen?: This is an interactive art installation about climate change and rising sea levels. It creates a rain effect through the melting of ice blocks, gradually submerging a city located at the bottom of the installation.
Black is Beautiful : Each article of clothing that we wear symbolizes something significant in history. What it means to us today, creates history.
The starry sky: The starry sky that breathes
Last Night Memory: Using different storytelling methods in one interactive film to create empathy and understanding between characters and the audience.
Salsa Y Cafe : The exploration of the connection between digital media and physical media and how that connection can educate a user about something new, while providing a comforting environment

Haptic Memory: Haptic Memory is an immersive experience that explores the psychosomatic impacts of our memories by combining first-person audio narratives scored with haptic reactions within a wearable device.
With/In No Particular Order: Interactive experience to quietly observe the arrangement of groups as they rearrange themselves.
